# Copy to .env and fill in. Used by server/index.js.
# Start API: cd server && node index.js (default PORT=4000). From repo root, npm run dev (or npm run preview)
# proxies /api to http://127.0.0.1:4000 so Crystal + globe API calls work without VITE_API_URL.
#
# --- Spotify (globe country panels, playlists, Crystal→Spotify matching) ---
# Server logs like `genre:latin year:2026` are Spotify Search API queries, not YouTube.
#
# --- YouTube Data API (Crystal Ball only: /api/youtube-*, embed playback in browser) ---
# Do not use for globe/country top tracks; those are Spotify-only.
#
# Luffa bot: LUFFA_BOT_SECRET (Robot Key). Optional: CLAUDE_API_KEY for AI intents/replies; without it, short text fallbacks are used.
# LUFFA_DEBUG=1   # log every poll (HTTP + envelope counts); default is a quiet heartbeat ~every 15s when inbox is empty
# LUFFA_POLL_MS=700   # how often to call Luffa /receive (250–3000 ms; default 700). Faster = quicker terminal “inbox” lines, more requests.
# CLAUDE_API_KEY=
# LUFFA_BROADCAST_GROUP_UID=   # optional: group chat UID for broadcasts (digest, alerts, battles, playlist notifications). If unset, broadcasts go to all known DM users.
# Showcase (instant demo triggers, any case): SHOWCASE-DIGEST | SHOWCASE-ALERT | SHOWCASE-BATTLE | SHOWCASE-PLAYLIST | SHOWCASE-MOOD
# Crystal Ball YouTube: YOUTUBE_API_KEY (+ optional YOUTUBE_API_KEY_2) — Google Cloud, enable YouTube Data API v3.
# Crystal: max ms per video for Spotify search before skipping (default 22000). Skipped rows are not added to playlists.
# CRYSTAL_SPOTIFY_LOOKUP_MS=22000
# Crystal “Archive session” saves JSON to ../archive/ (gitignored *.json).

LUFFA_BOT_SECRET=
YOUTUBE_API_KEY=
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=
SPOTIFY_REFRESH_TOKEN=
